  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws targeting money laundering. In the United States, key anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to report suspicious transactions and implement compliance programs to detect and prevent money laundering. Internationally, organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) set standards and guidelines for combating money laundering globally.",
